villa</link>.  <p>

A <b>Roman villa</b> is a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../526/342526.xml">
villa</link> that was built or lived in during the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../816/25816.xml">
Roman republic</link> and the <country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../507/25507.xml">
Roman Empire</link></country>
. A villa was originally a <site wordnetid="108651247" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../458/25458.xml">
Roman</link></village>
</site>
 <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../933/1312933.xml">
country house</link> built for the upper class. According to <skilled_worker wordnetid="110605985" confidence="0.8">
